{"key":"processedPost-6336833","value":{"id":6336833,"first":6336614,"last":6343113,"when":1165354658,"utime":"12/05/06 11:37 PM","content":"By the way, the reason for NOT shaking at inoculation is when the spores are widely diffused in a substrate, you force the slower growing monokaryons to travel long distances to find a compatible hyphae to pair up with, slowing down the whole process.  If you don't shake, your mycelium can look for a girlfriend right in the same area it germinates in, speeding up the process because dikaryons grow much faster than monokaryons.<br />RR","title":"Re: SHAKING IT","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}